Text.SourceString: How was your weekend? Im going to start this week off with a cup of the tavern's coffee..
I got them over the weekend and left it to chill in the fridge.. I keep the empty cups and use them as planters
You must have plenty of work to get your farm ready
Im no farmer but clearing weeds is probably the first step to do. Would you agree?
Your standard shyte will do..
If you want to upgrade any of your tools, bring them over to Sanchez' shop.. They know what they're doing.
They live across from my house in the woodlands
I guess we never really need any. There hasnt been any crime here, and the town has been around for a long time.. Its safe here.
I trust the islanders. They're all good people..
I will admit to you, TV shopping can get addictive
I should probably change the buletin today and make sure there arent any outdated posts.
If you want to keep track of people's birthday, there is a calendar near the community center. Dont worry, I update it every season
Birthday presents are the quickest way to make friends. I particularly like sake. Heh heh
I wouldnt turn down some pineapple upside-down cake either..
Can you believe its almost the weekend already?
The week goes by really fast when you have fun or have a lot of things to do
Yours must fly by
Do you have any plans for the weekend?
Ah, I see.. I will probably go to Local Tavern tonight and catch up with the folks
Frank makes mean pasta as well.. the kids love it.
Have you watch the new advertisment yet? Luke has an eye for quality electronics, thats for sure
Preparing for the new week?
The weather is perfect for diving.
I need to visit Socket Electronics today and ask Luke where my new carpet is
Ah darn.. Socket is closed today
Im going to treat myself to a pineapple upside-down cake today.
Sam's carries different variety of crops every year.. I hope he brings back Durian next year
Heh heh.. its my guilty pleasure
I am rather busy. I have a lot of things in the agenda this season, but I still like to take fishing break here and there..
You should talk to Sunny at Beach Shack if you have any questions about fishing.
Yes, he's Oliver's dad.
Some of the islanders like to do a group yoga at the Community Center every Saturday morning
Of course you can join. Leah usually leads the class..
Happy thursday, Player!
Coral Island has a very fertile soil. You can grow almost anything here.
And the fishing of course. You can catch salmon at the sea all summer long.
We are incredibly blessed here with the weather, fertile soil and occasional rat problems. It is important for us to give back by taking care of Mother Nature
The rat problem could've been way worse. I heard from my other mayor's friend that it destroyed their community center. Thankfully its all restored.
Back in the day, I would spend my saturdays diving from sunrise to sundown..
The good old days..
Have you tried growing grass? You can cut them and it will automatically be deposited into your silo as animal feeds
Sometimes Ben in the forest has seeds that Sam doesnt carry.. Bens open late today, you know..
Ben closes in the Fall. He likes to go on adventures, that one..
hmm.. That is true.. His eyes do always look red. He must not sleep very much.. That young man must have plenty of work to do.
I might go and say hi to him next week..
I think the last time I went to your farm was when you first moved into the island. Do you remember that?
It feels like ages ago. You've become a part of the community now
Part of my job is to check in on local business, to make sure that they are doing okay and on time with their taxes.
I've spoken to the Governor about lowering our taxes here or increase school budget
It really isnt my place to change those but there is nothing wrong with trying.
Should we put another community garden? I can see it being very helpful to the islanders
But Im not sure how I can get the funding for that.. Its a bit tight with us trying to keep our festivals running every year. The Governor may not like the idea very much.
I used to run a general shop downtown back in my youth. But then Mayor Leanne passed away.
In one of the towns meetings, I decided to ask if I should try running for her replacement. There seemed to be support for me, so I did.
Im proud to say that we have really good doctors living in here.
Im sure in a matter of time, Coral Island will attract more talented people, like you.
I have spent my life taking care of Coral Island. I never got to take Carol to Blora, now Im spending a lot of nights regretting it.
Now I dont feel like going traveling anymore, because if its just me, is it even worth it?
Another week is right around the corner. Are you planting anything new?
There is always less work in the weekend, except for when we hold festivals.
I have seen this town getting panicked about the flu outbreak. People were worried about stocking food.
We got them contained quickly and the histeria settled. But it was one expensive year for the town.
Its nice to see the youth are getting more and more involved in the community
You are setting up a great example for all of us, Player. Keep up the good job!
To tell you the truth, my favorite part about the town's meeting is seeing how united we are to tackle problems after problems.
I really think that we have enough garbage bins around the island. What do you think?
Thank you for helping with the leaking problem, Player. Many of the town's buildings are old, so leaking is pretty much expected.
I just hope the community center isnt next. We just cleared up the rats problem.
To tell you the truth, my favorite part about the town's meeting is seeing how united we are to tackle problems after problems.
I really think that we have enough garbage bins around the island. What do you think?
Not so long ago, your farm was run by a family of farmers. They retired and moved to a valley 3 islands over.
They used to exclusively plant seasonal berries and flowers, and nothing else.
Part of being a mayor of a small town is to collect local taxes.
Yes. I've heard that not all Mayors do that. I think every region has a different rule, but I dont mind doing it, given our small size.
Part of being a mayor of a small town is to collect local taxes.
Yes. I've heard that not all Mayors do that. I think every region has a different rule, but I dont mind doing it, given our small size.
Wine is wine. Whether they are good or bad, they taste the same to me.
Remember to only drink them in moderation.
I have managed this town for one too many years. Sometimes I think of what my life wouldve been like if I never run for office.
In retrospect, I should've traveled more..
How was your first week at the farm? its been awhile since someone stays at that cabin.
Im not too happy to announce Pufferfish's arrival next week. But the islanders need to know and to be honest, the branch manager, Karen is a delight to have

The space that they will occupy is actually theirs to begin with. The Governor let me know that they were planning to purchase your farm, but it seems like you beat them to it. So they come here to buy another spot themselves now
Pufferfish is looking to start drilling our island. They are interested in getting as much oil as possible to expand their business
They are building a mini golf for the community and trying to be part of us. So I think if we are not selling, we have nothing to worry about.
Have you plant any Spring seeds yet? Sugarcane is my personal favorite.
It does take a while to grow, but we grow the sweetest sugarcane around the islands. Im sure Sam would pay a lot of gold for it..
Spring is my least favorite season, because you know.. tax filing.. heh heh
Well, that was harsh of me. Spring is great actually.. Colorful peonies, tulips, sprauting around the island.. Bamboo shoots!
Are you ready for Summer? The beach is very vibrant that time of year!
You should keep some of your Spring vegetables in a chest, in case you need them sometime..
Collecting too many tax documents can be mentally demanding at times.. its good to get them done early
Summer is here!! Ah I can feel the sun on my skin! Life's good eh?
Are you going to plant pinapples this Summer? Sam might have the seeds this year..
Im glad Nina comes to visit. I remember when she was born. The celebration party was out of this world..
I usually spend my summer weekend at Beach Shack with the fellas, and catching up with Nina
I think Im going to visit the Sanchez tomorrow
They are a lot of fun to chat with. That Pablo always has some stories
How's the farm doing? I hope the old house is holding up okay..
I havent seen a rain this hard since....hmm..
Since the last time it rained, I guess. Apologies, rainy days make my head a bit fussy.
I cant hear you!! Lets get indoor and continue to chat!!
There is something soothing about rainy nights..
No matter the season, it gets quiet cold when it rains here..
*he seems to be hurrying somewhere, he probably didnt hear me*
Holy Doly! Its been awhile since it storms like this!
*he seems to be hurrying somewhere, he probably didnt hear me*
How are your plants holding up during the storm?
*he seems to be hurrying somewhere, he probably didnt hear me*
Doesnt this town covered in snow like this remind you of that town from that movie?!
umm.. cant think of the name. but you know what im talking about. the famous movie.. with the snow and the town..
Anywho, hows your day been?
Doesnt this town covered in snow like this remind you of that town from that movie?!
umm.. cant think of the name. but you know what im talking about. the famous movie.. with the snow and the town..
Anywho, hows your day been?
Good day, Player! Im happy to see the locals are supporting each other
I just had a nice chat next door and I thought I came here to check out what Luke has in store
How's the farm doing? I hope the old house is holding up okay..
*murmer to self* Do I really need a new blender?
Yes I do..
Im picking up some donation from Socket. Luke is a very charitable young man..
I buy extra kitchen appliances when I have the money and ship them off to woman shelter to celebrate Carol's life..
She never once forgot where she came from
I have been sporting this hairstyle since I was 18. People seem to like it..
Hi Player! enjoying yourself?
I've heard people say dont mix business with pleasure. Well I dont know what to tell ya, but Im here to check up on local business. Does it ever stop me from enjoying myself?
Nope. Im about to show you how much fun Im having. Just hang on longer, you dont wanna miss my classic dance moves.
I used to be quite the fun machine back in the day.
Heh.. heh.. heh.. Ive heard that stories at least 3 times now and it seems like it gets funnier and funnier each time.
The graveyard is their work too.. They always refuse payments for gravestones, but I must insist sometimes because I know they can really use the money..
Its my favorite spot in this house..
Especially after Carol's passing, I try not to spend too much time in the bedroom.
You know Player, some nights I sleep with my back towards my wife's side of the bed.. That way it feels like she's still here with me.
I would give anything to have one more day with her. One more chance to just sit and watch TV.. we dont even need to talk.
I miss her..
The beach is exceptionally beautiful this time of year..
The sea right here,Player, is a home to many creatures..
fancy a room for a gateaway weekend?
Just collecting data from Suki to monitor our tourism industry.. and restocking our town's brochures for the guests
Luke helped me made them. It can use a new design though.. This one is rather outdated.
Do you know Joko and Dinda well?
Have you tried their pinapple upside down cakes?
Sam doesnt give discount. Ive known him for years and years, never have I ever been given some sort of markdown or a rebate for crying out loud.
Well, OK. Sam carries the best produce, and to be fair, his price isnt too bad.. So, youre right. I really cant complain, can i.
Got all you need?
Unbelieve view from here
